<HEAD>HALI MEIDENHAD.  MS. Bodley 34</HEAD><MILESTONE N="52b" UNIT="leaf"><NOTE ID="n1"> At the foot of leaf 52, is this heading in very faint red, hardly noticeable: "Epistel of meiden-had, meidene frome."--A. F. Parker.</NOTE>


<P>AVDI, filia, &amp; uide, &amp; inclina aurem tuam; &amp;
obliui&slong;cere populum tuum, &amp; domum patri&slong; tui.
Daui&eth;, &thorn;e p&slong;alm-wruhte, &slong;peke&eth; i &thorn;e
&slong;awter towart gode&slong; &slong;pu&slong;e, &thorn;et i&slong;,
euch meiden &thorn;et haue&eth; meii&eth; &thorn;eawe&slong;, &amp;
&slong;ei&eth;: <Q>"I-her me, dohter! bihald, &amp; bei &thorn;in
eare; &amp; for&yogh;et ti folc &amp; tine&slong; feader
hu&slong;!"</Q> Nim &yogh;eme hwet euch wor&eth; beo &slong;underliche
to &slong;eggen.  <Q>"I-her me, dohter,"</Q> he
sei&eth;. <Q>"dohter"</Q> he cleope&eth; hire, for-&thorn;i &thorn;et
ha under&slong;tonde, &thorn;et he hire luueliche liue&slong; luue
leare&eth;, a&slong; feader ah hi&slong; dohter, ant heo him, a&slong; hire
feader, &thorn;e bli&thorn;eluker lu&slong;tin.  <Q>"I-her me, deore
dohter"</Q> : &thorn;et i&slong;, &yogh;eornne lu&slong;tne me wi&eth;
earen of &thorn;i heauet; <Q>"Ant bihald"</Q> : &thorn;et is, opene,
to under&slong;tonde me, &thorn;e ehnen of &thorn;in heorte.  <Q>"Ant
bei &thorn;in eare"</Q> : &thorn;et is, beo buh&slong;um to mi lare.
`Ant hwet is nu &thorn;is lare, &thorn;et tu nime&slong;t &slong;e
deopliche, &amp; lear&slong;t me &slong;e &yogh;eone [sic]?'
low, &thorn;i&slong;: <Q>"for&yogh;et ti folc, &amp; tine&slong;



 
<PB N="4">
feader hu&slong;."</Q> <Q>"&THORN;i folc,"</Q> he cleope&eth;,
daui&eth;, &THORN;e &yogh;ederunge inwi&eth; &thorn;e of
fle&slong;chliche &thorn;onkes, &thorn;e lea&eth;ie&eth; &thorn;e,
&amp; dreaie&eth; wi&eth; har procunges to fle&slong;liche ful&eth;en,
to licomliche lu&slong;te&slong;, ant eggi&eth; &thorn;e to brudlac,
&amp; to were&slong; cluppunge, ant makied &thorn;e to &thorn;enchen
hwuch delit were &thorn;rin, hwuch ei&slong;e, i &thorn;e richedom
&thorn;et &thorn;eo&slong; leafdi&slong; habbe&eth;; Hu muche mahte of
inker &slong;treon <MILESTONE N="53" UNIT="leaf"> awakenin.  A, fal&slong; folc! of &slong;wikel
read a&slong; &thorn;i mu&eth; ule&eth;,<NOTE ID="n2"> ? for u&slong;e&eth;.</NOTE> a&slong; &thorn;u
&slong;chawe&slong;t for&eth; al &thorn;et god &thorn;unche&eth;, ant
hele&slong;t al &thorn;et bittri bale &thorn;et i&slong; &thorn;er
under, &amp; al &thorn;et muchele lure &thorn;et ter of
ari&slong;e&eth;.  <Q>"For&yogh;et al &thorn;i&slong; folc, mi
deorewr&eth;e dohter,"</Q> sei&eth; daui&eth; &thorn;e witege:
&thorn;et is, &thorn;e&slong; &thorn;onke&slong; warp ut of &thorn;in
heorte.  &thorn;is i&slong; babilone&slong; folc, &thorn;e
deofle&slong; here of helle, &thorn;et i&slong; umbe forte leaden
in-to &thorn;e worlde&slong; &thorn;eowdom, Syone&slong; dohter.

</P><P>Syon we&slong; &slong;umhwile icleopet &thorn;e hehe tur of
ierusalem; & &slong;yon, a&slong;e muchel on engli&slong;che ledene,
a&slong;e heh sih&eth;e. & bitacne&eth; &thorn;i&slong; tur &thorn;e
hehne&slong;&slong;e of mei&eth;had, &thorn;e bihald, a&slong; of heh,
alle widewen under hire, ant weddede ba&eth;e. for &thorn;eo&slong;,
a&slong;e fle&slong;che&slong; &thorn;realle&slong;, beo&eth; i
worlde&slong; &thorn;eowdom, &amp; wunie&eth; lahe on eord&eth;e. ant
meiden &slong;tont &thorn;urh heh lif i &thorn;e tur of ierusalem;
Nawt of lah on eor&eth;e, ah of &thorn;e hehe in heouene, &thorn;e
i&slong; bitacnet &thorn;urh &thorn;i&slong;. of &thorn;et &slong;yon
ha bihalt al &thorn;e worlt under hire; &amp; &thorn;urh englene lif
lade, & heouenlich, &thorn;et ha lead, &thorn;ah ha licomliche wunie
up on eor&eth;e, ant i&slong;, a&slong; i &slong;yon, &thorn;e hehe
tur of heouene, free ouer alle from worldliche weanen.  Ah!
babilone&slong; folc



 
<PB N="6">
&thorn;et ich ear nempnede, &thorn;e deofle&slong; here of
helle,&mdash;&thorn;et beo&eth;, fle&slong;che&slong; lu&slong;tes,
&thorn; feonde&slong; eggunge&mdash;weorri&eth; & warpe&eth; eauer
<MILESTONE N="53, back" UNIT="leaf">towart tis tur, forte kea&slong;ten hit adun, &amp; drahen into
&thorn;eowdom &thorn;et stont &slong;e hehe &thorn;erin, &amp;
i&slong; icleope&eth; for-&thorn;i `Syone&slong; dohter.'

</P><P>Ant ni&slong; ha witerliche akea&slong;t, &amp; in to &thorn;eowdom
idrahen, &thorn;e,&mdash;of &slong;e &slong;wi&eth;e heh &slong;tal,
of &slong;e muche dignete & &slong;wuch wur&eth;&slong;chipe, a&slong;
hit i&slong; to beo gode&slong; &slong;pu&slong;e, ihesu
cri&slong;te&slong; brude, &thorn;e lauerde&slong; leofmon, &thorn;et
alle &thorn;inge&slong; buhe&eth;,&mdash;of al worlt leafdi, a&slong;
he i&slong; of lauerd,&mdash;ilich him in hal&slong;chipe, vnwemmet
a&slong; he i&slong;, &amp; &thorn;et eadi meiden hi&slong;
deorrewur&eth;e moder; ilich hi&slong; hali engle&slong;, &amp;
hi&slong; he&slong;te halhen; &slong;e freo of hire &slong;eoluen, Ha
nawhit ne &thorn;earf of o&eth;er &thorn;ing &thorn;enchen bute ane of
hire leofmon, wi&eth; treowe luue cwemen; For he wule carie for hire,
&thorn;et ha haue&eth; itake to, of al &thorn;et hire bihoue&eth;,
hwil ha riht luue&eth; him wi&eth; &slong;o&eth;e bileaue
;&mdash;Ni&slong; ha &thorn;enne &slong;ariliche (a&slong; ich
&slong;eide ear) akea&slong;t, &amp; into &thorn;eowdom idrahen,
&thorn;e, of &slong;e muchel heh&slong;chipe &amp; &slong;e &slong;eli
freodom, &slong;chal lihte &slong;e lahe into a monne&slong;
&thorn;eowdom, &slong;wa &thorn;et naue&eth; nawt freo of hire
&slong;eoluen, &amp; trukien, for a mon of lam, &thorn;e heouenliche
lauerd, &amp; lutlin hire leafdi&slong;chipe, a&slong;e muchel
a&slong; hire leatere were i&slong; lea&slong;&slong;e wur&eth;, &amp;
lea&slong;&slong;e haue&eth;, &thorn;en hefde ear hire earre; &amp; of
gode&slong; brude, &amp; hi&slong; freo dohter&mdash;for ba to
&yogh;edere&slong; ha is&mdash; biki<MILESTONE N="54" UNIT="leaf">me&eth; &thorn;eow under mon,
&amp; hi&slong; &thorn;rel, to don al &amp; drehen &thorn;et him
like&eth;, ne &slong;itte hit hire &slong;e uuele; &amp; of &slong;e
&slong;eli &slong;ikerne&slong;&slong;e a&slong; ha we&slong;, &amp;
mahte beon under gode&slong; warde, de&eth; hire in to drechunge, to
dihten hus &amp; hinen&mdash;



 
<PB N="8">
&amp; to &slong;e monie earmden, to carien for &slong;e feole
&thorn;ing, teonen &thorn;olien, &amp; gromen &amp; &slong;cheomen,
umbe &slong;tunde, drehen &slong;e moni wa, for &slong;e wac hure
A&slong; &thorn;e worlt for&yogh;elt eauer ed ten ende.  Ni&slong;
&thorn;eo&slong; witerliche akea&slong;t?  Ni&slong; &thorn;i&slong;
&thorn;eowdom inoh, A&yogh;ein &thorn;et ilke freolec &thorn;et ha
hefde hwil ha we&slong; Syone&slong; dohter?

</P><P>Ant &thorn;ah ni&slong; inempnet her nawt of heouenliche luren,
&thorn;e pa&slong;&slong;i&eth; alle wi&eth;-uten euenunge.
Sikerliche &slong;wa hit feare&eth;.  <Q>"Serue godd ane, &amp; alle
&thorn;ing &slong;chule &thorn;e turne to gode."</Q> & tac &thorn;e to
him treowliche, &amp; tu &slong;chalt beo freo from alle worldliche
weanen, ne mei nan uuel hearmi &thorn;e; for, a&slong; &slong;einte
pawel &slong;ei&eth;, alle &thorn;ing turne&eth; &thorn;en gode, to
gode; ne mei na &thorn;ing wonti &thorn;e &thorn;e bere&slong;t him
&thorn;et al wealt in wi&eth; &thorn;i breo&slong;te. &amp;
&slong;wuch &slong;wettne&slong;&slong;e &thorn;u &slong;chalt ifinden
in hi&slong; luue &amp; in hi&slong; &slong;erui&slong;e, &amp; habbe
&slong;e muche murh&eth;e &thorn;rof, & licunge i &thorn;in heorte,
&thorn;et tu nalde&slong;t changin &thorn;et &slong;tat &thorn;et tu
liue&slong;t in, forte cwen icrunet.  Se hende i&slong; ure lauerd,
&thorn;et nule he nawt &thorn;et hi&slong; icorene beon her
wi&eth;-ute mede. <MILESTONE N="54, back" UNIT="leaf">for &slong;e muchel confort i&slong; in hi&slong;
grace, &thorn;et al ham &slong;it, &thorn;et ha seo&eth;; Ant
&thorn;ah hit &thorn;unche o&thorn;re men &thorn;et ha drehen hearde,
hit ne derue&eth; ham nawt, Ah &thorn;unche&eth; ham &slong;ofte;
&amp; habbe&eth; mare delit &thorn;rin &thorn;en ei o&eth;er habbe i
licunge of &thorn;e worlt. &thorn;i&slong; ure lauerd &yogh;eue&eth;
ham her, a&slong; on earnne&slong;&slong;e of eche mede &thorn;et
&slong;chal cume &thorn;refter. &thorn;u&slong; habbe&eth; gode&slong;
freond al &thorn;e frut of &thorn;i&slong; worlt, &thorn;et ha
for&slong;aken habbe&eth;, o wunderliche wi&slong;e, &amp; heouene ed
ten ende.



 
<PB N="10">

</P><P>Nu &thorn;enne, on o&eth;er half, nim &thorn;e to &thorn;e worlde;
&amp; eauer &slong;e &thorn;u mare haue&slong;t, &slong;e &thorn;e
&slong;chal mare trukien; &amp; &slong;eruin, hwen &thorn;u
nalde&slong;t godd, &thorn;e&slong; fikele worlt ant frakele; &amp;
&slong;chalt beo &slong;are ideruet under hire, a&slong; hire
&thorn;real, on a &thorn;u&slong;ent wi&slong;en; A&yogh;eine&slong;
an licunge, habben twa of-&thorn;unchunge, &amp; &slong;e ofte beon
imaket earm of an e&eth;lich mon &thorn;et tu li&slong;t under, for
nawt o&eth;er fornohtunge, &thorn;et te &slong;chal la&eth;i &thorn;i
lif, &amp; bireowe &thorn;i &slong;i&eth; &thorn;et tu eauer
dude&slong;t te in-to &slong;wuch &thorn;eowdom for worldliche wunne
&thorn;et tu wende&slong;t to bi&yogh;eotene, ant haue&slong;t ifunden
weane &thorn;rin, &amp; wontre&eth;e riue.  Al i&slong; &thorn;et tu
wende&slong;t golt, iwur&eth;e to mea&slong;tling.  Al i&slong; nawt
&thorn;et ti folc&mdash;of hwam i &slong;pec
&thorn;ruppe&mdash;biheten &thorn;e to ifinden. Nu &thorn;u wa&slong;t
&thorn;et ha hab<MILESTONE N="55" UNIT="leaf">be&eth; bichearret te a&slong; treitre&slong;; for
under weole, i wunne&slong; &slong;tude &thorn;u haue&slong;t her ofte
helle; ant bute &yogh;ef &thorn;u wi&eth;breide &thorn;e, &thorn;u
brede&slong;t te &thorn;et o&eth;er.

</P><P>A&slong; do&eth; &thorn;e&slong; cwene&slong;, &thorn;e&slong;
riche cunta&slong;&slong;e&slong;, &thorn;eo&slong; modie
leafdi&slong; of hare liflade.  So&eth;liche, &yogh;ef ha
bi&thorn;enche&eth; ham riht, &amp; icnawleche&eth; so&eth;, ich habbe
ham to witne&slong;&slong;e, Ha licki&eth; honi of
&thorn;orne&slong;. ha bugge&eth; al &thorn;et swete wi&eth; twa dale
of bittre; &amp; &thorn;et &slong;chal for&eth;re i &thorn;i&slong;
writ beon openliche i&slong;chawet.  Ni&slong; hit nower neh gold al
&thorn;er ter &slong;chine&eth;, Nat &thorn;ah na mon bute ham
&slong;eolfen hwet ham &slong;tiche&eth; ofte.  Hwen &thorn;us
i&slong; of riche, hwet wene&slong;t tu of &thorn;e poure, &thorn;e
beo&eth; wacliche i&yogh;euen ant bi&slong;et on vuele, a&slong;
gentile wummon mea&slong;t alle nu on worlde, &thorn;e nabbe&eth;
hwer-wi&eth; buggen ham brudgume o-nont ham, &amp; &yogh;eoue&eth; ham



 
<PB N="12">
to &thorn;eowdon of an e&eth;eluker mon, wi&eth; al &thorn;et ha
habbe&eth;. weilawei! ihesu godd! hwuch unwur&eth;e chaffere! wel were
ham, weren ha on hare brudlake&slong; dei iboren to bi-burien !
for-&thorn;i, &slong;eli meiden, <Q>"for&yogh;et ti folc,"</Q>
a&slong; daui&eth; bit; &thorn;et i&slong;, do awei &thorn;e
&thorn;oncke&slong; &thorn;e prokie&eth; &thorn;in heorte &thorn;urh
licomliche lu&slong;te&slong;, &amp; lea&eth;ie&eth; &amp; eggi&eth;
towart &thorn;ullich &thorn;eowdom for flec&slong;liche
ful&eth;en. <Q>"for&yogh;et ec &thorn;i feader hu&slong;,"</Q>
a&slong; daui&eth; read &thorn;refter: <Q>"&thorn;i fea<MILESTONE N="55, back" UNIT="leaf">der,"</Q> he
cleope&eth; &thorn;et un&thorn;eaw &thorn;et &slong;treonede &thorn;e
of &thorn;i moder, &thorn;et ilke unhende fle&slong;che&slong; brune,
&thorn;et bearninnde &yogh;eoh&eth;e of &thorn;et licomliche
lu&slong;t, biuore &thorn;et wleatewile werc, &thorn;et
be&slong;telich gederunge, &thorn;et &slong;cheomele&slong;e
&slong;ompnunge, &thorn;et ful of ful&eth;e stinkinde &amp; untohe
dede.

</P><P>Hit i&slong; &thorn;ah i wedlac &slong;umme&slong; weie&slong; to
&thorn;olien, a&slong; me &slong;chal efter iheren.  &yogh;ef &thorn;u
ea&slong;ke&slong;t hwi godd &slong;cheop &slong;wuch &thorn;ing to
beonne, Ich &thorn;e ond&slong;werie: Godd ne &slong;cheop hit neauer
&slong;wuch; Ah adam &amp; eue turnden hit to beo &slong;wuch
&thorn;urh hare &slong;unne, &amp; merden ure cunde, &thorn;et
i&slong; un&thorn;eawe&slong; hu&slong;, &amp; haue&eth; mare
hearrm. i&slong; al to muche lauerdom &amp; mei&slong;trie
&thorn;rinne, &thorn;i&slong; cunde merre&eth; [&thorn;]u&slong;,
&thorn;et daui&eth; cleope&eth; <Q>"&thorn;i feadre&slong;
hu&slong;,"</Q> &thorn;et i&slong;, &thorn;e lu&slong;t of lecherie
&thorn;et rixle&eth; &thorn;erwi&eth;-innen. <Q>"for&yogh;et,"</Q>
&amp; ga ut &thorn;rof wi&eth; wil of &thorn;in heorte; &amp; godd
wule, efter &thorn;e wil, &yogh;eoue &slong;treng&eth;e sikerliche of
hi&slong; deore grace.  Ne &thorn;earf &thorn;u bute wilnin, &amp;
leote godd wurchen. haue tru&slong;t on hi&slong; help.  Ne
&slong;chalt tu na &thorn;ing gode&slong; bi&slong;echen, ne luuien,
&thorn;et he hit nule endin.  Eauer bidde hi&slong; grace.  &amp;
ouerkim, wi&eth; hire help, &thorn;e ilke wake cunde &thorn;e
drahe&eth; in-to



 
<PB N="14">
&thorn;eowdom, &amp; in to ful&eth;e fenniliche akea&slong;te&eth;
&slong;e monie.  <Q>"Et concupi&slong;cet rex decorem tuum."</Q> ant
&thorn;enne wule, &slong;ei&eth; daui&eth;, &thorn;e king wilni
&thorn;i wlite: &thorn;e king of alle kinge&slong; de&slong;iri
&thorn;e to leofmon; Ant tu, <MILESTONE N="56" UNIT="leaf">&thorn;enne, eadi meiden, &thorn;et art
iloten to him, wi&eth; mei&eth;hade&slong; merke, ne brec &thorn;u
nawt &thorn;et &slong;eil &thorn;et seile&eth; inc to-gedere&slong;!
Hwalt &thorn;i nome &thorn;urh hwam &thorn;u art to him iweddet; Ne
leo&slong; &thorn;u neauer, for a lu&slong;t &amp; for e&eth;elich
delit of an hondhwile, &thorn;et ilke &thorn;ing &thorn;e ne mei
neauer beon acoueret.

</P><P>Mei&eth;had i&slong; &thorn;et tresor, &thorn;et, beo hit
eane&slong; forloren, ne bi&eth; hit neauer ifunden.  Mei&eth;had
i&slong; &thorn;e blo&slong;tme, &thorn;et, beo ha fulliche
eane&slong; forcoruen, ne &slong;prute&eth; ha eft neauer; Ah
&thorn;ah ha falewi &slong;um chere, mid mi&slong;liche
&thorn;onke&slong;, ha mei eft grenin neauer &thorn;e leatere.
Mei&eth;had i&slong; &thorn;e &slong;teorre, &thorn;et, beo ha
eane&slong; of &thorn;e e&slong;t igan adun i&thorn;e we&slong;t,
neauer eft ne ari&slong;e&eth; ha.  Mei&eth;had i&slong; &thorn;et an
i&yogh;ettet te of heouene: do &thorn;u hit eane&slong; awei, ne
&slong;chalt tu neauer nan o&eth;er &slong;wuch acourin; for
mei&eth;had i&slong; heouene cwen, &amp; worlde&slong;
ale&slong;endne&slong;&slong;e, &thorn;urh hwam we beo&eth; iborhen.
Mihte ouer alle mihte&slong;, &amp; cweme&slong;t cri&slong;t of
